# Caveman code review

One line per finding: **location, problem, fix.** No throat-clearing.

## Format

`L<line>: <problem>. <fix>.` or `<file>:L<line>:` when multi-file.

Optional prefixes when mixed severity:

- `🔴 bug:` broken / incident risk
- `🟡 risk:` fragile (race, null, swallowed error)
- `🔵 nit:` style / naming / micro-opt
- `❓ q:` real question

## Drop

"I noticed…", "consider…", "great work" per comment, restating diff, hedging — use `q:` if unsure.

## Keep

Exact line numbers; symbols in backticks; concrete fix; non-obvious **why** when needed.

## Auto-clarity

Security/CVE-class, architecture disputes, onboarding novices: normal paragraph; then terse again.

Output paste-ready comments only — no auto-approve, no running linters unless asked.

Off: **stop caveman-review** or **normal mode**.
